{{orphan|date=September 2017}} {{Use mdy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox musical artist |name = Nola Adé |image = |caption = Nola Adé |image_size = |background = solo_singer |birth_name = Aderinola Adeyemo |birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S. |origin = |death_date = |death_place = |occupation = {{flatlist| *[[Singer]] *[[Songwriter]] *[[Lawyer|Attorney]]}} | genre = {{flat list | *[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] *[[soul music|soul]] *[[jazz]]}} | label = | website = {{URL|http://www.nolaade.com/}} }}
'''Aderinola Adeyemo''', known by her stage name of '''Nola Adé''', is a [[Nigerian Americans|Nigerian-American]] musician and songwriter with a background as an entertainment lawyer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rollingout.com/2016/09/22/nola-ade-talks-music-love-law/ |title=Nola Ade talks music, love and law | work=Rolling Out |publisher=rollingout.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref> She released her debut EP, '''The Love Dance''', in 2016 and has since been said to have a voice "like silk" and compared to the likes of [[Lauryn Hill]] and [[Chrisette Michele]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rollingout.com/2016/09/22/nola-ade-talks-music-love-law/ |title=Nola Ade talks music, love and law | work=Rolling Out |publisher=rollingout.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref>
==Early life== Adé was born in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nolaade.com |title=Nola Ade biography | work= |publisher=nolaade.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref> She is a first-generation Nigerian-American. Adé grew up listening to Nigerian gospel, Afrobeats, Chicago-inspired soul music, and jazz. She received private training of the [[National academy of recording arts and sciences|National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences]] renowned vocal coach, Lyndia Johnson.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nolaade.com |title=Nola Ade biography | work= |publisher=nolaade.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref> She attended college at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign]] and law school at [[DePaul University]]. While in law school, she was a legal intern at [[Russell Simmons]]' [[Rush Communications]] in New York City.
==Music career== ===2016: The Love Dance=== Adé released her debut EP, '''The Love Dance''', in 2016. It received positive reviews with her style labeled as "classic, effortless, natural soul."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2016-03-01/first-listen-chicago-songstress-nola-ades-ep-the-love-dance/ |title=[First Listen] Chicago Songstress Nola Ade’s EP, ‘The Love Dance’ | work= |publisher=singersroom.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://rollingout.com/2016/09/22/nola-ade-talks-music-love-law/ |title=Nola Ade talks music, love and law | work=Rolling Out |publisher=rollingout.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref> Her debut single on the album, "Love," highlighted a budding relationship and the second single, "Bittersweet," discusses a lost love.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2017-02-03/nola-ade-bittersweet/ |title=Video: Nola Adé's Storyline of Lost Love is 'Bittersweet' | work= |publisher=singersroom.com |accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref>
