{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox video game | title = The Deadly Tower of Monsters | image = Deadly Tower of Monsters cover.jpg | developer = [[ACE Team]] | publisher = [[Atlus USA]] | engine = [[Unreal Engine 3]] | platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] | released = {{Video game release|WW|19 January 2016}} | genre = [[Top-down shooter]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] }}
'''''The Deadly Tower of Monsters''''' is a [[science fiction]] [[top-down shooter]] [[video game]] developed by [[ACE Team]] and published by [[Atlus USA]], which released for [[Microsoft Windows]] and [[PlayStation 4]] on 19 January 2016.
== Gameplay == {{expand-section|date=November 2016}} ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' is a top-down shooter with twin-stick controls and melee combat elements. A jetpack can be used to reach high areas.<ref name="Destructoid">{{cite web | url = https://www.destructoid.com/review-the-deadly-tower-of-monsters-334028.phtml | title = Review: The Deadly Tower of Monsters | last = Carter | first = Chris | date = 19 January 2016 | website = [[Destructoid]] | publisher = [[ModernMethod]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref>
== Plot == ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' follows three actors in the movie of the same name. It is inspired by 1950's [[science fiction]] movies.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.siliconera.com/2015/12/03/atlus-launches-1970s-sci-fi-game-the-deadly-tower-of-monsters-on-january-19th/ | title = Atlus Launches 1970s Sci-Fi Game The Deadly Tower Of Monsters On January 19th | last = Priestman | first = Chris | date = 3 December 2015 | website = [[Siliconera]] | publisher = [[Curse, Inc.]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref>
The game's [[framing device]] is that of an early 1970s [[B-movie]] ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' recently released on DVD, with the director's commentary of its in-universe director Dan Smith serving as a combination of tutorial and meta-commentary on the game, providing an explanation as to why many default elements of shooters would be in what is ostensibly a film (the player being required to break boxes to obtain items, for example, is taken as the lead actor [[ad-libbing]] on Smith's advice to make sure every moment was somewhat exciting). The film itself is a space opera in which astronaut Dick Starspeed (played in-universe by actor Jonathan Digby) being shot down on an alien planet ruled by a tyrannical emperor.
== Development == ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' was announced on 12 June 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/06/12/deadly-tower-of-monsters-zeno-clash-devs/ | title = ACE Team's The Deadly Tower Of Monsters Announced | last = O'Connor | first = Alice | date = 12 June 2015 | website = [[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref> A trailer was released on 2 December 2015. The game was released on 19 January 2016.
== Reception == ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' received mostly positive reviews. The game has a score of 73/100 on [[Metacritic]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/the-deadly-tower-of-monsters/critic-reviews | title = The Deadly Tower of Monsters Critic Reviews for PC | website = [[Metacritic]] | publisher = [[CBS Interactive]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref> ''[[Destructoid]]'' awarded it a score of 8 out of 10, saying "''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' is a fleeting experience, but one that no B-movie fan should go without."<ref name="Destructoid" /> [[PlayStation LifeStyle]] awarded it 7.5 out of 10, saying "Just like the movies it tries to emulate, the game is so bad with its special effects, dialogue, and set-pieces that it's rather good."<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2016/01/19/the-deadly-tower-of-monsters-review-so-bad-its-good/ | title = The Deadly Tower of Monsters Review – So Bad It's Good (PS4) | last = Honea | first = Keri | date = 19 January 2016 | website = [[PlayStation LifeStyle]] | publisher = [[CraveOnline]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref> ''[[Hardcore Gamer]]'' awarded it a 4 out of 5 saying "Minor issues aside, ''The Deadly Tower of Monsters'' is a pleasant surprise indeed and a particularly impressive budget action game showcasing a lot of creativity."<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2016/01/23/review-the-deadly-tower-of-monsters/188756/ | title = Review: The Deadly Tower of Monsters | last = LeClair | first = Kyle | date = 23 January 2016 | website = [[Hardcore Gamer]] | accessdate = 2 June 2016}}</ref>
