{{Infobox video game |title= The Sims 3: Into The Future |image= Sims3intothefutureboxart.jpg |developer=[[EA Salt Lake]] |publisher=[[Electronic Arts]] |series = ''[[The Sims]]'' |release = {{vgrelease|NA|October 22, 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://simsvip.com/2013/07/23/the-sims-3-into-the-future-release-date-102213/|title=The Sims 3 Into the Future Release Date|publisher=SimsVIP|date=July 23, 2013|accessdate=January 7, 2018}}</ref>|EU|October 24, 2013|UK|October 25, 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beyondsims.com/48189/into-the-future-release-date/|title=The Sims 3 Into the Future Release Date for UK and US|publisher=[[BeyondSims]]|accessdate=January 7, 2018|date=July 23, 2013}}</ref>}} |modes= [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] |platforms= [[OS X]], [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''The Sims 3: Into the Future''''' is the eleventh and final expansion pack for ''[[The Sims 3]]'' series from [[Electronic Arts]] and was released on October 22, 2013 in North America.<ref>{{cite web|date=May 6, 2013|url=http://simsvip.com/2013/05/06/future-themed-ep-last-game-for-sims-3-series/|title="Future Themed" EP, Last Game for Sims 3 Series|accessdate=January 7, 2018}}</ref> It is available for both [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] and [[Mac OS X|OS X]]. In Europe it was released on October 24, 2013 and in the United Kingdom on October 25, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Sims 3 goes back ... back to the future|url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/07/23/the-sims-3-goes-back-back-to-the-future/|website=[[Engadget]]|date=July 23, 2013|accessdate=January 7, 2018}}</ref>
==Gameplay== The expansion is [[futuristic]] themed. Upon installation, players may be visited by a time traveller in their home neighborhood, who gives their sims his time portal for use upon receiving help from the player. Using this portal, sims can travel to the future, into a new sub-neighborhood called "Oasis Landing", a futuristic town built amongst mountainous wastelands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://simsvip.com/2013/07/23/sims-3-into-the-future-fact-sheet-official-screens/|title=Sims 3 Into the Future Fact Sheet + Official Screens|date=July 23, 2013|accessdate=January 7, 2018|publisher=SimsVIP}}</ref>
Plumbots (similar to simbots and servos in previous sim games) are a major addition to the expansion. They can be built and fully customized with the new "Create-A-Bot" mode, and players can create various trait chips that determines their personality, use and gameplay. Hoverboards, jetpacks, [[monorails]] and hovercars are introduced to the game as new [[transportation]] options. New careers include [[astronomers]] and bot dealers. New objects include [[holographic]] TVs, food synthesizers, build-a-bot workshops and the laser rythimacon, a new instrument.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gb.thesims3.com/community/blog.html?blogid=513639|title=The Sims 3 Community Blog: Let's go...INTO THE FUTURE!!|date=July 30, 2013|accessdate=January 7, 2018|website=thesims3.com|publisher=Electronic Arts}}</ref>
Sims are also able to visit their future [[Lineal descendant|descendant]]s during time travel, and can change or eliminate these descendants altogether if the player sends the sim back to the present and changes their lifestyle or fate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thesims.com/en_GB/the-sims-3-into-the-future|title=The Sims™ 3 Into the Future|accessdate=August 13, 2013|publisher=Electronic Arts|website=thesims.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130814000446/http://thesims.com/en_GB/the-sims-3-into-the-future|archivedate=August 14, 2013|df=}}</ref>
==Development== On January 8, 2013, it was revealed on the live broadcast that [[Electronic Arts]] plans to release a futuristic-themed expansion pack which was still in the early stages of development.<ref>{{cite web|date=January 8, 2013|url=http://investor.ea.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=732234|title=EA Reveals The Sims 3 Line-Up for 2013 Including New Expansion and Stuff Packs|accessdate=January 7, 2018|publisher=Electronic Arts}}</ref>
